<!-- Purpose: To test the INPUT element with the TYPE attribute set to CHECKBOX and the CHECKED attribute set to checked. -->

<!-- Expected result: When the page is displayed, the 2nd and third options should be pre-selected, submitting should result in a return page displaying the 2nd and 3rd checkboxes selected. -->

</head>

<body>

<p>Options 2 and 3 should be pre-selected, un-checking the boxes and

selecting reload should result in the checkboxes being reset.</p>



<form method="post" action="post-query.cgi"><input type="checkbox"

name="pets" value="bird" /> bird<br />

 <input type="checkbox" name="pets" value="cat"

checked="checked" /> cat<br />

 <input type="checkbox" name="pets" value="dog"

checked="checked" /> dog<br />

 <input type="reset" /> <input type="submit" /></form>

